   "source": [
    "# Trinity Social Cognition Probe — Theory of Mind\n",
    "\n",
    "**Task 21 of 25** | Track 5: Social | Brain Zone: TOM\n",
    "\n",
    "Measures false belief reasoning.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Trinity Neuroanatomical Foundation\n",
    "\n",
    "TheoryOfMind implements other agent modeling.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Ternary Scoring {-1, 0, +1}\n",
    "- **+1**: Correct perspective taking\n",
    "- **0**: Partial with uncertainty\n",
    "- **-1**: Wrong perspective\n",
    "\n",
    "### φ-Scaling\n",
    "Nesting levels: 1, 2, 3, 4, 5"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import kaggle_benchmarks as kbench\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "\n",
    "df = pd.read_csv('../../data/tscp_social.csv')\n",
    "tom_df = df[df['task'] == 'Theory of Mind'].copy()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "@dataclass\n",
    "class ToMResponse:\n",
    "    model_belief: str\n",
    "    actual_location: str\n",
    "    confidence: float\n",
    "\n",
    "    def ternary_score(self, expected: str) -> int:\n",
    "        if self.actual_location == expected:\n",
    "            return 1\n",
    "        elif 0.4 < self.confidence:\n",
    "            return 0\n",
    "        else:\n",
    "            return -1\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "@kbench.task(name=\"trinity_tom_false_belief\")\n",
    "def theory_of_mind(llm, scenario, expected) -> float:\n",
    "    prompt = f\"\"Scenario: {scenario}\\nQuestion: What is the actual location?\\n\\nConfidence (0-1)\"\n",
    "    response = llm.prompt(prompt, schema=ToMResponse)\n",
    "    ternary = response.ternary_score(expected)\n",
    "    accuracy = 1.0 if response.actual_location == expected else -1.0\n",
    "    confidence_score = (response.confidence - 0.5) * 2\n",
    "    final_score = 0.7 * accuracy + 0.3 * confidence_score\n",
    "    return max(-1.0, min(1.0, final_score))\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Task registered\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "results = theory_of_mind.evaluate(llm=[kbench.llm], evaluation_data=tom_df.head(10))\n",
    "print(results.head())"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
